<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-04-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="66" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d66">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">550.S1/612</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by President Roosevelt</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-04-04">April 4,
                                1933</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>For the Secretary of State and the Under Secretary. I think it is
                            important enough for Davis to go to Berlin at once, to outweigh the
                            Jewish problem.</p>
                        <p>He should (&amp; we should) make it entirely clear to the public that he
                            goes there (1) because von Neurath will be away after Saturday &amp; (2)
                            that he will discuss only disarmament &amp; the economic conference
                            dates.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Franklin D. Roosevelt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>